# NOTICE — Third-party and upstream components

Evocode (Эвокод) is a product shell combining:

1. **Evocode Core** — privacy plane, DLP, skill router, local runtime attach
   (this repository; see LICENSE — MIT).

2. **VSCodium / Code - OSS** — IDE base (MIT).
   https://github.com/VSCodium/vscodium
   Bundled or built via `packages/ide/` bootstrap; not all upstream sources are
   committed here.

3. **Kilocode / OpenCode lineage** — agent extension runtime (MIT / Apache as
   published upstream). Rebranded UI and provider wiring live under
   `packages/agent-extension/`. Upstream monorepo is **not** vendored by default;
   set `KILO_SRC` and run `npm run bootstrap:agent`.

4. **llama.cpp and forks** (ik_llama, buun-llama-cpp, etc.) — local inference
   binaries referenced only by path in `config/profiles.json`. Weights (GGUF)
   are never copied into this repo.

5. **Skill corpus** under `skills/system/` — mixed provenance:
   - First-party `evocode-*` skills (MIT, same as this project).
   - Community and imported skills may carry their own LICENSE / LICENSE.txt
     inside each skill folder. See `skills/NOTICE.md`.

Do not assume every skill file is original Evocode content. When redistributing
a subset of skills, retain the corresponding per-skill license files.

Trademarks: “VS Code”, “Kilo”, “OpenCode”, and model names belong to their
respective owners. Evocode is an independent local-first product, not affiliated
with Microsoft, Anthropic, or OpenAI.
